---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Tending the Ember';
const subtitle = 'For days when you feel low, heavy, depressed, or numb.';
const duration = '2 Hours · 7:00 – 9:00';
---
<Base title={title} description={subtitle}>
  <article class="etude-page">
    <header class="etude-head">
      <p class="etude-kicker">Etude · Restorative</p>
      <h1 class="etude-title">{title}</h1>
      <p class="etude-relief">{subtitle}</p>
      <p class="etude-duration">{duration}</p>
      <nav class="etude-nav">
        <a href="/etudes/restorative/">← restorative etudes</a>
        <span class="etude-nav-sep">·</span>
        <a href="/puzzles/the-partition-problem/">puzzle</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <section class="etude-intro">
      <p class="etude-section-label">When to reach for this routine</p>
      <p>You feel heavy. Something was taken, or something hasn’t arrived. The temptation is to skip practice. Don’t. This routine meets you on the floor. It does not ask you to be strong — only to show up while the ember stays lit. Winter turns.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="etude-stage">
      <div class="etude-card etude-card-prelude">
        <p class="etude-step">Warm-Ups (Optional)</p>
        <p class="etude-card-context">Begin lying down if needed. Shoulder shrugs, spinal circles, neck rolls.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="etude-card etude-card-prelude">
        <p class="etude-step">Pranayama — Extended Exhale Pranayama (4:8 Calming Breath)</p>
        <p class="etude-card-context">Inhale four. Exhale eight. The long exhale activates the parasympathetic — signals safety to a body that has been bracing.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="etude-segment-label">Poses — Root to Crown</p>

      <p class="etude-chakra"><span class="etude-chakra-mark">◆</span> Muladhara — I am still here. That is enough.</p>

      <div class="etude-card">
        <p class="etude-step">Pose 1 of 4</p>
        <h2 class="etude-card-title">Balasana – Child’s Pose (Reverse Wall Version)</h2>
        <p class="etude-pose-time">7:15 – 7:32</p>
        <p class="etude-pose-benefits">Benefits – Calms the mind; relieves lower back tension; weight of thighs against belly provides grounding compression; stimulates digestive system; Root. Cautions – Hip or knee issues; pregnancy — use standard Child’s Pose with wide knees. Alt: Balasana – Floor Version; Balasana – Reverse Chair Version.</p>
        <blockquote class="etude-pose-quote">“I relax from outer involvement into my inner haven of peace.”</blockquote>
        <p class="etude-card-context">Side 2: radiate to soul-friends, known and yet to be known.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="etude-chakra"><span class="etude-chakra-mark">◆</span> Vishuddha — My truth has value. I am not invisible.</p>

      <div class="etude-card">
        <p class="etude-step">Pose 2 of 4</p>
        <h2 class="etude-card-title">Heart Opener – Supported Backbend</h2>
        <p class="etude-pose-time">8:28 – 8:43</p>
        <p class="etude-pose-benefits">Benefits – Opens chest, throat, and collarbones; activates Heart; counteracts forward-collapsing posture; promotes expansion of awareness. Cautions – Heart conditions; neck injuries; spondylolisthesis; pregnancy. Lower block if neck uncomfortable. Alt: Reclined Pose; Mountain Brook.</p>
        <blockquote class="etude-pose-quote">“With calm faith, I open to Thy Light.”</blockquote>
        <p class="etude-card-context">You don’t have to say anything today. Let the chest open. The light is there.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="etude-chakra"><span class="etude-chakra-mark">◆</span> Ajna → Sahasrara — I trust the larger arc of my life.</p>

      <div class="etude-card">
        <p class="etude-step">Pose 3 of 4</p>
        <h2 class="etude-card-title">Viparita Karani – Simple</h2>
        <p class="etude-pose-time">8:43 – 8:53</p>
        <p class="etude-pose-benefits">Benefits – Drains excess fluid from legs; reduces exhaustion and fatigue; deeply calming for nervous and cardiovascular systems; gentle and accessible on hard days. Cautions – Glaucoma; serious neck injuries; pregnancy after first trimester. Alt: Instant Maui; Savasana – Simple.</p>
        <blockquote class="etude-pose-quote">“Awake, my sleeping powers, awake!”</blockquote>
        <p class="etude-card-context">The ember is not out. You are tending it right now.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="etude-chakra"><span class="etude-chakra-mark">◆</span> Sahasrara — I surrender the weight. I am held.</p>

      <div class="etude-card">
        <p class="etude-step">Pose 4 of 4</p>
        <h2 class="etude-card-title">Savasana – Side Lying Pose • Final Relaxation</h2>
        <p class="etude-pose-time">8:53 – 9:00+</p>
        <p class="etude-pose-benefits">Benefits – Gentle containment for an overwhelmed nervous system; instinctively soothing for grief and heaviness; integrates all previous poses; safe for all conditions including pregnancy. Cautions – Alternate sides for extended holds. Full support under head and between knees. Alt: Savasana – Burrito; Savasana – Stonehenge.</p>
        <blockquote class="etude-pose-quote">“Bones, muscles, movement I surrender now; anxiety, elation and depression, churning thoughts — all these I give into the hands of peace.”</blockquote>
        <p class="etude-card-context">You are allowed to rest. Small and steady is enough. The ember keeps itself.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="etude-card etude-card-prelude">
        <p class="etude-step">Exit cues</p>
        <p class="etude-card-context">Sense your body and the room. Wiggle fingers and toes. Roll to your back. Press up to seated. A few moments of quiet.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="etude-coda">
      <p class="etude-coda-label">Closing</p>
      <p>Showing up on a hard day is the whole practice. Visualize someone in their own hard season; surround them with warm light. Offer the same to yourself. Thank yourself. Namaste.</p>
    </footer>
  </article>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  /* === etude page chrome === */
  .etude-page {
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .etude-head {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .etude-kicker {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .etude-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .etude-relief {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .etude-duration {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .etude-nav {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .etude-nav a { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .etude-nav a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .etude-nav-sep { margin: 0 0.5rem; opacity: 0.5; }

  .etude-intro {
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }
  .etude-intro p {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .etude-section-label {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .etude-segment-label {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 1.4rem 0 0.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.55rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .etude-stage {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.1rem;
  }

  /* === pose / segment cards === */
  .etude-card {
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.4rem;
  }
  .etude-card-prelude {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem 1.2rem;
  }
  .etude-step {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .etude-card-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .etude-pose-time {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    margin: 0 0 0.95rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .etude-pose-benefits {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .etude-pose-quote {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding-left: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0.85rem 0 1rem;
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .etude-card-context {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* === chakra banner — small-caps label vocabulary === */
  .etude-chakra {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 1.4rem 0 0;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem;
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    border-radius: 8px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .etude-chakra-mark {
    margin-right: 0.45rem;
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  /* === coda === */
  .etude-coda {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .etude-coda-label {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
  }
  .etude-coda p:not(.etude-coda-label) {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* === mobile === */
  @media (max-width: 32rem) {
    .etude-title { font-size: 1.85rem; }
    .etude-card { padding: 1.15rem 1.1rem 1.1rem; border-radius: 10px; }
    .etude-card-prelude { padding: 1rem 1.1rem; }
    .etude-card-title { font-size: 1.3rem; }
    .etude-chakra { font-size: 0.78rem; padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; }
    .etude-pose-quote { padding-left: 0.8rem; }
  }

  /* === print === */
  @media print {
    .etude-page {
      max-width: none;
      color: #000;
    }
    .etude-nav { display: none; }
    .etude-stage { gap: 0.6rem; }
    .etude-card,
    .etude-card-prelude,
    .etude-chakra {
      background: transparent;
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 0.75rem 0.9rem;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .etude-chakra {
      border: none;
      border-left: 3px solid #999;
      border-radius: 0;
      color: #000;
    }
    .etude-segment-label {
      border-bottom: 1px solid #999;
      color: #000;
    }
    .etude-pose-quote {
      border-left: 2px solid #999;
    }
    .etude-coda {
      border-top: 1px solid #999;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .etude-title { font-size: 1.6rem; }
    .etude-card-title { font-size: 1.15rem; }
  }
</style>
